      {
        "id": 3192592,
        "name": "Shay Aldriedge",
        "username": "Shay_A",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/b77776/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-07-05T21:49:30.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I had the pleasure of enjoying one of these about 6 weeks ago. It was poured alongside a \u201895 Trotanoy (both poured in to decanters), and the Trotanoy absolutely blew it out of the water\u2026for the first two hours. Between hour 3 and beyond, the Haut Brion came roaring to life in a big way and ended up outshining the Trotanoy.</p>\n<p>I think it\u2019s quite fine the first few hours, but in the event you get the fireworks we did, I\u2019d recommend 3hrs.</p>\n<p>Just a small sample size as this is my only experience with the \u201895 HB. Congrats to your brother! Regardless of the decant, I\u2019m sure it will be a memorable evening.</p>",
