      {
        "id": 3192602,
        "name": "Jonathan Jetter",
        "username": "Jonathan_Jetter",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/f07891/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-07-05T22:11:55.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"171844\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>While 95 is not the 89, I\u2019d be careful about buying something like H-B at a screaming deal price. This is not a niche bottle that would be difficult to move or a bottle that needs the \u201cright\u201d collector to come along. It has pretty predictable value, and H-B will always be H-B \u2026 especially a \u201cpristine\u201d bottle.</p>\n<p>Your brother\u2019s engagement is a special occasion, and you\u2019re thoughtful for treating him to such a fantastic bottle of wine. Just a quick word of caution before jumping in with two feet or getting tunnel vision on a single bottle. I\u2019d only buy such a bottle from a trusted source no matter the price.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I hear you on that, yes.</p>\n<p>It\u2019s not necessarily a \u201cscreaming deal\u201d price, but a small bit below (edit: actually right at) the Winesearcher low, from a shop that doesn\u2019t seem to be listed there, and is right here in NYC.</p>\n<p>I trust the retailer, never done anything quite this expensive from them, but everything I\u2019ve bought from them has been good, and most of their other prices are around the Winesearcher low.</p>\n<p>I have other stuff on hand as a backup plan if needed, and in the worst case, it\u2019s NYC, I can go buy anything w/ a little effort.</p>",
